Saucony Shadow 6000 Alife (2022)
data.story: The ALIFE x Saucony Shadow 6000 ‘NYC Subway Maps’ reunites the partner brands on a retro runner originally released in 1991. The sneaker carries a white open-mesh upper with metallic silver accents on the side logo and heel tab, featuring ‘New York’ inscribed in green lettering across the left and right shoe. The city’s MTA subway lines are represented through the multi-colored suede overlays that enliven the collar, eyestay and heel. A dual-branded woven tag adorns the exposed foam tongue, while a crimson ALIFE logo appears on the lateral forefoot.

data.name: Saucony Jazz 81 X Hommework by Trinidad James
data.story: Designed in collaboration with Trinidad James’ apparel brand, the Hommewrk x Saucony Jazz 81 ‘Trinidadian Heritage’ features a distinctive two-tone palette inspired by Sorrel, a beverage made with dried hibiscus petals. The upper is constructed from crimson tumbled leather with color-matched suede on the eyestay and heel panel. Pink semi-translucent TPU lands on the forefoot overlay, river logo and heel tab, marked with ‘HMME’ and ‘WRK’ across the left and right shoe. A two-tone EVA midsole offers lightweight cushioning and a smooth ride.

data.name: Azura Lite 'Ski Jacket - Light Blue'
data.story: The Saucony Azura Lite Ski Jacket ‘Light Blue’ revives the late ‘80s runner with a winter-ready build inspired by a vintage nylon bomber jacket. The upper is constructed from teal-colored textile with tonal suede overlays and a warm faux fur lining. Contrasting hits of purple land on the eyestay, toe box and river logo. They’re joined by bright crimson accents on the heel and molded upper eyelets. The sneaker rides on a cushy EVA midsole, supported by a lugged rubber outsole and Saucony’s Torsional Rigidity Bar.

data.story: The Saucony Shadow 6000 ‘Licorice’ treats the retro runner to a confectionary color scheme. Black and white mesh is executed on the upper, reinforced with candy-bright pink suede overlays and secured with rope laces inspired by black licorice. Additional hits of color arrive via mustard yellow suede eyestays and aqua-colored textile on the interior lining. The lightweight build rests on a PWRRUN+ midsole, supported by a two-tone rubber outsole equipped with triangular lugs.

data.name: Hornet 'White Vapor'
data.story: The Saucony Hornet ‘White Vapor’ brings back an archival ‘70s runner in a neutral design devoid of all color. Shoring up the breathable white mesh upper are contrasting black suede overlays at the forefoot, heel and eyestay. Grey synthetic leather is utilized on the sneaker’s curvilinear logo and heel tab, marked with a Saucony wordmark in white lettering. The sneaker sits atop a white EVA midsole, featuring a classic wedge shape and reinforced by a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Boston Children's Hospital x Jazz 81 'Fiona'
data.story: The Boston Children’s Hospital x Saucony Jazz 81 ‘Fiona’ launched as part of the Run for Good Children’s Program, an initiative that recognizes children’s hospitals around the US and Canada, and showcases unique creations designed by kids. This pair features a white nylon upper secured with multicolor laces and bolstered with orange leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Bright blue accents make their way to the satin lining and leather river logo, while a photo collage decorates the heel tab and sockliner. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole is fitted with triangular lugs for optimal grip.

data.name: Hornet 'Black Grey'
data.story: The Saucony Hornet ‘Black Grey’ applies neutral tones to a vintage running shoe originally released in 1975. The ventilated upper is crafted from grey mesh with black suede paneling on the forefoot, heel and eyestay. Accented with three cut-out circles, Saucony’s river logo adorns the quarter panel in white synthetic leather. A matching white Saucony wordmark is stamped on a green leather heel tab, giving the shoe an unexpected pop of color. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a white EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Hornet 'Tan Navy'
data.story: The Saucony Hornet ‘Tan Navy’ revives the vintage ‘70s runner with classic materials and color blocking. The breathable blue mesh upper features a white leather river logo and off-white suede overlays at the forefoot, heel and eyestay. Bright yellow accents land on the leather heel tab and sockliner, both marked with Saucony branding. The sneaker sits on a wedge-shaped EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a gum rubber outsole with a herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 6000 Up There Doors to the World
data.story: Designed in collaboration with the Melbourne-based retailer, the Up There x Saucony Shadow 6000 ‘Doors To The World’ is inspired by world travel, and more specifically, the brightly colored tiles and doors found throughout the European continent. The upper blends open off-white mesh with olive green suede overlays and Saucony’s river logo in fuchsia patent leather. Passport-inspired graphics are stamped on the tongue and sockliner. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

Hornet 'White Black'
data.story: The Saucony Hornet ‘White Black’ brings back a vintage running shoe that originally debuted in 1975. The upper is crafted from breathable white mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. Saucony’s signature river logo adorns the quarter panel in black synthetic leather. Matching black hits land on the heel tab and woven tongue tag. The sneaker rests on a full-length EVA midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Jazz 81 Black Green
data.story: The Saucony Jazz 81 ‘Black Green’ showcases a simple two-tone palette on an updated edition of the original Jazz silhouette. A charcoal grey finish is applied to the upper, constructed from ripstop nylon with tonal Wolverine suede overlays. Emerald accents settle on the leather heel tab and Saucony’s classic river logo. Atop the lightly padded tongue, a woven tag displays archival Saucony badging from 1981. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a speckled EVA midsole, reinforced by a lugged blown rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Peregrine 11 Astrotrail Pack Earth
data.story: The Saucony Peregrine 11 ‘Earth’ is drawn from the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ composed of four trail shoes inspired by the four universal elements of western astrology. This pair makes use of a beige textile upper with a reinforced toe cap and contrasting green synthetic heel overlay. Zodiac symbols representing the earth signs adorn a webbing pull tab attached to the breathable mesh tongue. The sneaker rests on a speckled PWRRUN midsole, supported underfoot by a lugged PWRTRAC outsole designed specifically for rugged terrain.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Astrotrail Pack Air
data.story: Launching as part of the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ the Saucony Shadow 5000 ‘Air’ represents one of the four universal elements featured in western astrology. A speed lacing system secures the upper, composed of magenta-colored nylon with tan suede overlays, an orange leather heel tab and Saucony’s signature river logo in stitched blue leather. Atop the tongue, the webbing pull tab displays the three astrological air signs. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a speckled EVA midsole.

data.name: Saucony Mad River 2 TR Astrotrail Pack Water
data.story: The Saucony Mad River 2 TR ‘Water’ is taken from the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ featuring a quartet of trail running shoes inspired by astrology and the four elements of the natural world. This pair showcases a gradient two-tone finish on a breathable textile upper, reinforced with synthetic overlays and secured with a drawcord lacing system. Common to all four models in the collection are a speckled midsole and a birthstone zodiac symbol on the webbing pull tab affixed to the tongue.

data.name: Saucony Grid Azura Astrotrail Pack Fire
data.story: The Saucony Grid Azura ‘Fire’ is one of four colorways that comprise the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ featuring trail running shoes inspired by the universal four elements of western astrology. This pair applies a series of toothy tan suede overlays to a nylon upper finished in a gradient blend of yellow and orange. The sneaker’s utilitarian aesthetic is enhanced via a bungee drawcord lacing system and an added webbing pull tab atop the tongue, decorated with the three fire signs of the zodiac. A speckled foam midsole is supported underfoot by a decoupled purple rubber outsole, featuring triangle-shaped lugs for durable grip.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Court RFG Natural
data.story: Designed with sustainability in mind, the Saucony Jazz Court RFG ‘Natural’ is built with a total of seven natural materials and zero plastic. A woven jute upper is reinforced with canvas overlays and lined in sheep wool, colored with dye sourced from blue gardenia flowers. The sneaker’s laces are made with eucalyptus-tree fiber. In lieu of synthetic adhesives, a true sidewall stitch is used to attach the upper to the semi-translucent gum rubber cupsole. The kicks are packaged in a 100% recycled carboard box.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Court White Black
data.story: The Saucony Jazz Court ‘White Black’ treats the vintage silhouette to an essential two-tone color scheme. The low-top’s white leather upper is accented with contrasting black detailing on the woven tongue tag, Saucony-branded heel tab and signature river logo on the quarter panel. A perforated toe box offers improved breathability, while an anti-microbial lining keeps feet feeling fresh. Underfoot, a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Court White Green
data.story: The Saucony Jazz Court ‘White Green’ is clad in a standard white leather upper with forest green accents. They take the form of Saucony’s signature river logo, as well as a suede heel tab and woven tongue tag. An off-white rubber midsole enhances the shoe’s vintage aesthetic, while an encapsulated EVA foam wedge provides lightweight cushioning. A gum rubber outsole, complete with a pivot point and herringbone traction pattern, yields maximum grip.

data.name: Wmns Shamrock Kinvara 12 'St. Patrick's Day'
data.story: The Saucony women’s Shamrock Kinvara 12 ‘St. Patrick’s Day’ celebrates March 17 with playful graphics plastered across the interior and exterior of the lightweight running shoe. The emerald-colored mesh upper, covered in an all-over argyle print with four-leaf clover details, sits atop a matching green PWRRUN midsole streaked with gold. Inside the shoe, an additional nod to the fabled pot of gold takes the form of a gold-coin print on the interior tongue, collar lining and insole.

data.name: Saucony Azura 2000 END. The Brain
data.story: Designed in collaboration with the UK-based retailer, the END. x Saucony Azura 2000 ‘The Brain’ draws inspiration from the eponymous complex organ. The sneaker’s layered composition incorporates a mesh base in a vibrant pink hue, visible through a mono-mesh side window and contrasted by a series of toothy grey suede overlays throughout. The cerebral theme continues on the dual-branded woven tongue tag, custom sockliner and translucent rubber outsole.

Saucony Endorphin Shift White Mutant
data.story: The Saucony Endorphin Shift ‘White Mutant’ highlights vibrant accents on an easy-going running shoe laden with plush cushioning. Neon yellow laces secure the Formfit upper, constructed from breathable mesh that conforms to the individual contours of the foot. The lightweight build is mounted on a stacked PWRRUN midsole, featuring an innovative foam compound that’s lighter, more flexible, and more responsive than the brand’s previous foam cushioning technologies.

data.name: Echelon 8 Wide 'Black'
data.story: The Saucony Echelon 8 Wide ‘Black’ delivers a performance running shoe that packs a secure fit with responsive cushioning. Metallic silver branding elements stand out on a Formfit upper built with breathable black mesh. A roomy toe box is designed to accommodate foot splay, while a 3D heel counter provides rearfoot stability. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a PWRRUN foam midsole, supported by Saucony’s pressure-dispersing Tri-flex rubber outsole.

data.name: Omni 19 'Fog Citrus'
data.story: The Saucony Omni 19 ‘Fog Citrus’ highlights a subdued palette on a performance runner built with a generous fit and lightweight support. The Formfit upper uses breathable engineered mesh that adapts to the contours of the foot. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length foam midsole, equipped with an extended medial post for improved stability and control. An unexpected flash of neon yellow makes its way to the Tri-flex rubber outsole, designed to disperse pressure evenly while providing grippy traction.

data.name: Omni 19 'Indigo'
data.story: The Saucony Omni 19 ‘Indigo’ highlights varying shades of blue on the Formfit upper, constructed from engineered mesh that hugs the foot for a locked-in fit. A TPU heel counter delivers rearfoot stability, while the wider toe box provides adequate room to accommodate toe splay. The lightweight running shoe is mounted on a full-length foam midsole, reinforced by a Tri-flex rubber outsole that offers an optimal blend of grippy traction, flexibility and pressure dispersion.

data.name: Endorphin Shift 'Black Grey'
data.story: The Saucony Endorphin Shift ‘Black Grey’ applies neutral tones to a running shoe built with Speedroll technology, designed to make running easier through a built-in, propulsive stance. The knit textile upper is enlivened with a skull graphic on the toe box and fortified with a smoky translucent overlay that wraps around the heel. Springy cushioning arrives via a bulky yet lightweight PWRRUN midsole, featuring a foam compound that pairs EVA with polyurethane.

data.name: Omni 19 'Alloy'
data.story: The Saucony Omni 19 ‘Alloy’ showcases neutral grey tones on a performance running shoe that delivers a smooth, stable ride. Breathable engineered mesh is utilized on the upper, fortified with seamless synthetic overlays and a molded TPU heel counter. The lightweight build sits atop a stacked foam midsole, featuring an extended medial post for added control. Underfoot, the Tri-flex rubber outsole allows for improved ground contact and pressure distribution.

data.name: Omni 19 'Black White'
data.story: The Saucony Omni 19 ‘Black White’ delivers a stable ride in a subdued package. Neutral tones suffuse the Formfit upper, constructed from engineered mesh that adapts to the contours of the foot. Synthetic overlays provide lightweight, seamless support, while a TPU heel counter is designed to hug the back of the foot. A resilient foam midsole is fortified with an extended medial post for enhanced control. Underfoot, a Tri-flex rubber outsole provides enhanced ground contact and pressure distribution.

data.name: Saucony Endorphin Shift Future
data.story: The Saucony Endorphin Shift ‘Future’ pairs an easy-going run with an eye-catching design. Vibrant bursts of color stand out on a streamlined Formfit upper, constructed from black knit textile and engineered to deliver a locked-in fit. A blend of responsive and supportive cushioning is provided by a PWRRUN midsole, featuring a propulsive Speedroll geometry that delivers a rolling feel with every stride. Underfoot, multicolored carbon rubber in high-wear areas delivers grippy traction.

data.name: Saucony Endorphin Shift Black White
data.story: The Saucony Endorphin Shift ‘Black White’ delivers a monochromatic take on a performance trainer built for easy-going runs. The Formfit knit upper is designed to provide a supportive, locked-in fit, with webbing pull tabs at the tongue and heel for easy on and off. The lightweight build rests on a stacked PWRRUN midsole, featuring propulsive, Speedroll geometry for perpetual forward momentum. Underfoot, carbon rubber is placed in high-wear areas for durable traction.

data.name: Echelon 8 Wide 'Alloy'
data.story: The Saucony Echelon 8 Wide ‘Alloy’ combines a stable ride with a roomy, comfortable fit. A subtle grey finish is executed on an engineered mesh upper, shaped with a wider toe box to allow for foot splay. A 3D heel counter cradles the back of the foot, while tonal synthetic overlays provide lightweight support and added durability. A plush Foundation Platform insole acts in tandem with a PWRRUN midsole to deliver springy cushioning with each step.

data.name: Triumph 18 'Black Gum'
data.story: The Saucony Triumph 18 ‘Black Gum’ applies a monotone design to a performance running shoe that delivers an ultra-responsive ride. The supportive Formfit upper is constructed from black engineered mesh with tonal 3D print overlays for strategic flexibility and structure. TPU beads make up the composition of the PWRRUN+ midsole, featuring bouncier and more durable cushioning than standard EVA foams. Underfoot, a gum rubber Triflex outsole provides optimal grip.

data.name: Saucony Kinvara 12 Icon
data.story: The Saucony Kinvara 12 ‘Icon’ is taken from a celebratory five-piece pack marking the 40th anniversary of the Saucony Jazz. The vintage runner’s retro aesthetic is applied to this Kinvara 12 colorway, featuring a one-piece textile upper in navy and slate blue. Saucony’s River logo adorns the quarter panel in metallic silver, while the brand’s Running Man icon is captured on the woven tongue tag. The sneaker rides on a springy PWRRUN midsole, reinforced underfoot with durable rubber in high-wear areas.

The lightweight upper, featuring a classic blend of nylon and suede, adds two-tone rope laces and a webbing pull tab for a distinct outdoor aesthetic. It all rides on a speckled EVA foam midsole, reinforced underfoot with Saucony’s Maxitrac triangular lug outsole for durable traction.

The mixed-material build rests on a speckled black foam midsole, equipped with Saucony’s signature Grid cushioning.

The premium suede and leather upper is finished in a refined Bone White Shade, complete with whip-stitched moc toe detailing, calfskin leather lining and a sherpa-lined tongue. The midsole, built with genuine cork and lightweight EVA, rides atop a rippled gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid Azura 2000 OG (2020)

The sneaker’s breathable mesh upper is dominated by a series of wavy black overlays that create a sawtooth design from heel to toe. At the quarter panel, a see-through mono-mesh window is accented with Saucony’s logo in blue and neon green.

data.name: Saucony Aya Raised By Wolves
data.story: Made in collaboration with the Canadian streetwear brand, the Raised By Wolves x AYA 'Asphalt Jungle' makes use of a previously discontinued Saucony runner form the ‘90s. The design draws inspiration from skateboarding culture during the same decade, highlighted by a dark grey finish on an upper built with nearly a dozen different materials, including mesh, ripstop and suede. Contrasting pops of color appear on the collar lining and interior tongue, the latter featuring a concealed stash pocket.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Feature Dreamland
data.story: Unveiled in October 2019, the Feature x Saucony 'Dreamland' capsule is an homage to Area 51. The Shadow 5000's tumbled leather, perforated nubuck and suede upper is illuminated via reflective accents and a glow-in-the-dark logo on the midfoot. The sneaker includes a hazard heel tab, co-signed tongue label and heat-map insole. A pop of translucent neon to the rubber outsole completes the extraterrestrial inspiration.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD 24 Kilates La Victoria
data.story: Drawing inspiration from the first ship to travel around the world, 24 Kilates worked with Saucony to deliver the 24 Kilates x Grid SD 'La Victoria' in October 2019. The contemporary remake features a burnished brown leather upper with perforated panels and contrasting dark brown and blue accents. Building on the concept, a white ripstop tongue is emblematic of the ship's sail while brass grommets hit the sidewall for ventilation. A flag design and branding at the heel complete the nautical motif.

data.name: Sneaker x Jazz Original 'Carolina Mustard'
data.story: South Carolina boutique retailer, Sneaker collaborated with sneaker brand, Saucony on National Mustard Day, August 3rd, 2019, to launch the Sneaker x Jazz Original 'Carolina Mustard' streetwear shoe. Taking the Jazz silhouette and giving it South Carolina flair, the shoe comes dressed in a yellow suede upper with leather detailing while nylon makes an appearance at the tongue and midfoot. An extra pair of checkered laces come in an accompanying 'sauce packet' to conclude the theme.

data.name: Saucony Grid Web White Grey Red
Saucony Grid Web White Multi
data.story: Bringing back their classic runner from 2000, sneaker brand, Saucony released the Grid Web Retro 'OG' 2019 in July 2019. The throwback model features a white mesh base with a web-like TPU cage surrounding the silhouette. Giving the shoe a dynamic design, hits of yellow, orange and blue accent the shoe while black lines make their way down the back. A sculpted midsole and durable midfoot shank team up with a super grippy rubber outsole to fortify the retro sneaker.

data.name: Saucony Aya White Blue
data.story: Revamping the 1994 classic, Saucony rereleased the Aya silhouette in July 2019. The low-top running sneaker is outfitted with a nylon upper and soft leather overlays to deliver structure and multi-directional agility. Taking on a 'White Blue' colorway, the lightweight runner features multiple lace-though options for a customizable fit. Up top, a padded collar and smooth tongue promote easy on and off, while a speckled midsole and rubber outsole continue the retro vibe below.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Original White Gum
data.story: For the original debut of the Saucony Jazz in 1981, the three-dot brand consulted an expert podiatrist to help create what would become one of their most recognizable silhouettes. Continuing to be a symbol of ingenuity, the updated July 2019 Jazz Original 'White Gum' version enlists a perforated leather upper with solid leather panels to reinforce the design. The midsole is constructed with responsive foam and sits atop a classic Maxitrac triangular lug outsole to promote balance and a sturdy ride.

data.name: Jazz Original 'Black Gum'
data.story: Hailing from the 1981 archives, the Saucony Jazz Original gets a makeover for this July 2019 release. Dressed in an all-black, premium leather upper, the classic silhouette features perforations throughout, allowing for superior airflow and lightweight comfort. A white signature three-dot logo along the midfoot provides contrast and a reminder of the brand's early days while a stacked EVA midsole and rubber gum outsole underfoot help to maintain control on versatile terrain.

data.name: Kith x Grid Web 'Slime Yellow'
data.story: Mixing contemporary Kith style with Saucony performance, the two brands released the Kith x Grid Web silhouette in June 2019. A lightweight mesh upper keeps the foot cool and dry and is supported by webbed 3M overlays to maintain stability. For a fresh take on the simple look, the 'Slime Yellow' sneaker is designed with vibrant branding details at the tongue and sidewall and a matching TPU midfoot arch in green.

data.name: Kith x Grid Web 'Grey Orange'
data.story: Taking NYC fashion to the streets, retail store, Kith joined Saucony to unveil the Kith x Grid Web lifestyle silhouette in June 2019. The casual favorite merges a breathable mesh upper with web-like, reflective 3M overlays across the foot in this 'Grey Orange' style. Blending sports shoe performance with an uptown feel, the low-top shoe incorporates a gradient effect on the branding details at the tongue, midfoot and TPU midfoot arch support while a multicolored outsole offers grip underfoot.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Politics Cafe Du Monde
Sneaker Politics x Cafe du Monde x Shadow 5000 'White Beignet'
Aya 'Purple Orange'
data.story: This Saucony Aya 'Purple Orange' sneaker arrived in June 2019 as a retro takedown of the 1994 classic. The shoe is named for speed—with 'Aya' meaning 'to fly swiftly'—and was originally engineered for running performance. This archival-modeled release is constructed with a purple mesh-based upper with stabilizing overlays in white and orange. A reflective section at the heel helps provide visibility in low-light conditions and a speckled EVA midsole delivers support.

data.name: Bodega x Azura 'Lucky 13'
data.story: Boston-based retailer, Bodega teamed up with Saucony to unveil the exclusive Bodega x Azura 'Lucky 13' running-meets-lifestyle silhouette in May 2019. Celebrating the brand's 13th birthday, the sneaker is decked out with layers of neoprene, suede, 3M fabric and mesh. The black upper is accented with hits of red and purple while the sidewall boasts branding detail in alternating black and pink hues. Underfoot, a speckled midsole and patterned rubber outsole continue the lucky vibe.

data.name: Azura OG 'Black Yellow'
data.story: The Saucony Azura OG sneaker salutes the retro runner in a line-for-line execution of its iconic 80s elements. Debuted in April 2019, this 'Black Yellow' makeover douses the ripstop mesh and microsuede upper in a retro palette. Signature logos embellish the tongue, heel and midfoot. A compression-molded EVA midsole, Torsional Rigidity bar and tricolored outsole conclude the athletic-inspired styling.

data.name: Azura 'Neo Tokyo'
data.story: A throwback to the 1988 runner, the Saucony Azura manipulates heritage lines in a contemporary remake. This 'Neo Tokyo' interpretation—released in April 2019—brandishes techno-charged hues on the microsuede and ripstop mesh upper. 80s styling goes full force with neon accents and signature branding codes. The full-length EVA midsole is stacked on top of a triangular lugged outsole split by a TPU stabilizer.

data.name: Saucony Kinvara 10 Dunkin (W)
data.story: A tribute to the Boston Marathon, the Dunkin' x Saucony Kinvara 10 'Classic Dunkin' Print' sneaker represents the symbiotic relationship between running, coffee and donuts. This women's variant—emerging in March 2019—carries a knitted upper with fading brand graphics. Special decals and an enameled medallion play up the whimsical vibe. The iconic color palette reappears on the EVA+ midsole and tri-flex rubberized outsole lugs.

data.name: Dunkin' x Kinvara 10 Kids 'Classic Dunkin' Print'
data.story: The Dunkin' x Saucony Kinvara 10 Kids 'Classic Dunkin' Print' sneaker celebrates the Boston Marathon race with cheeky references to the relationship between running and pastries. Issued in March 2019, playful logo graphics are rolled out on the knitted upper of this kid's version. Donut decals and a special aglet heighten the quirky expression. The chain's iconic color palette is repeated on the EVA+ midsole and rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Kinvara 10 Dunkin
data.story: Launched in March 2019, the Dunkin' x Saucony Kinvara 10 'Classic Dunkin' Print' sneaker is a cheeky commemoration of the year's historic Boston Marathon race. A repeating gradient logo sweeps across the lightweight knit upper, with playful donut and coffee cup icons donning the tongue, laces and heel. The chain's iconic color palette is further highlighted on the EVA+ midsole and tri-flex rubberized outsole lugs.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 White Purple
data.story: The Saucony Grid 9000 became a popular runner known for its forward-thinking technology. The Grid 9000 Premium Suede 'White Purple' sneaker blends the original’s retro flair with modern design. The March 2019 release features ventilated mesh underlays with suede and leather overlays. The Grid sole unit delivers enhanced cushioning and stability.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 White Blue
data.story: The Saucony Grid 9000 Premium Suede sneaker modernizes the 90s-born runner with technical equipment and stylish additions. Unveiled in March 2019, this 'Royal Blue' variant is engineered with a mesh underlay, suede paneling and a neoprene bootie. Simplified text branding is placed on the pull tab and quarter panel. An EVA midsole with the eponymous cushioning system and a durable rubber outsole are returned.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 6000 Avocado Toast
data.story: A performance and streetwear staple since the early 90s, the Saucony Shadow 6000 has seen countless iterations over time. A 2019 release, the Shadow 6000 'Avocado Toast' continues the heritage, with colorway based on millennials' favorite food. The upper of the limited edition sneaker comes in what the brand calls 'a toasted leather,' with a unique green taking over the top half. The 'red chile flake collar' tops off the look.

data.name: Azura OG '30th Anniversary'
data.story: To celebrate the 30th anniversary of the Azura OG, Saucony released a bold retro colorway in its original colors. The Azura OG '30th Anniversary' features a white breathable mesh-based upper with matching suede overlays along the forefoot and heel. The low top also boasts blue and yellow overlays throughout, embroidered Saucony branding on the lateral side, and an EVA midsole for responsive cushioning.

data.name: Grid SD 'Garden District'
data.story: Embracing the heritage of New Orleans, the ‘Garden District’ edition of the Saucony Grid SD uses an ultra-soft suede on the overlays and a cracked leather branding application to mirror the bleached look of the city’s homes and garden district. Breathable mesh underlays optimize airflow, while the tongue is stitched with the fleur-de-lis, which ties to the city’s longstanding French heritage.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 6000 Feature Living Fossil
data.story: Inspired by the Ichthyosaur, Nevada’s state fossil, the Feature x Shadow 6000 ‘Living Fossil’ dropped in June 2018 as a collaboration between Saucony and Las Vegas’ Feature Sneaker Boutique. The retro runner has a suede and nubuck upper, dressed in shades of Shonisaurus Grey, complete with a water-resistant toebox. Bright green holographic accents mark the heel and the signature dots on the Saucony logo, while the speckled midsole carries a black-green gradient effect.

data.name: END x Grid 8500 'Lobster'
data.story: Keeping in line with Saucony’s food-centric collaborations, this new Grid 8500 pays homage to lobster, their local delicacy. The model has a shellfish-inspired construction on the upper and outsole, with a shell-like mix of ‘Jaffa’ suede and ‘orange peel’ leather overlay. The design stays true to the lobster’s actual colors with a lobster claw print leather insole, and blue and orange lace options. The sneakers come in an original bright blue fishnet packaging to keep your lobster-inspired collectible secure.

data.name: Saucony Kinvara 9 Dunkin Donuts
data.story: Celebrating the Boston Marathon, this special-edition Saucony Kinvara 9 was designed in partnership with a veritable New England institution — Dunkin’ Donuts. The shoe dropped in March 2018, carrying a mostly white base with unique flourishes denoting Dunkin’ staples: cascading sprinkles and a frosted donut cover the heel, while the Saucony logo on the forefoot is modified with the addition of coffee beans. Additional Dunkin’ branding is found on the tongue and sockliner.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 EVR Solebox Pink Devil
Saucony Grid SD Woodburn
data.story: The Saucony Grid SD 'Woodburn' sneaker is a fresh take on the iconic runner, sporting elements reminiscent of the outdoors. Debuted in Fall 2017, this iteration flaunts a suede upper with a woodgrain graphic on the leather overlays. Three-hole detailing, reflective elements and synthetic quarter straps add a signature touch. A cushioned midsole and aggressive rubber outsole maintain the core aesthetic.

data.name: Saucony Grid 8500 Ramen
data.story: Saucony’s Grid 8500 draws influence from the Ramen delicacy, featuring a premium Miso Brown leather upper with a caramelized finish, while the mono-sock heel collar and quarter-panels are complemented with a braided application that resembles the traditional dish. The debossed tongue logos reference the porcelain bowls typically used for serving ramen noodles.

data.name: Saucony Shadow Master 5000 AFEW Goethe
data.story: Afew and Saucony teamed up on the Master 5000 silhouette for an exclusive rendition inspired by the poet Wolfgang Johann von Goethe, whose work is displayed at the iconic Goethe Museum. The rose and grey suede paneling pays homage to the design of the museum itself, which was built in 1763, while the heel showcases a script that references the writer’s work.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 6000 MD Space Pack
data.story: Inspired by the aesthetics of the space program, the Saucony Shadow 6000 MD 'Space' combines a 'dad shoe' vibe with a sleeker design aesthetic. The mesh and leather upper comes in a tri-tone colorway, with teal accents on the liner, several leather overlays and the Saucony logo taking up the side panel. Special branding lands on the heel, while the padded collar, Ionic Cushioning System and Stytherm heel counter all add cushioning and stability.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Originators Heskicks Turntable
data.story: Bringing together some of the most successful influencers in sneaker culture, the Saucony Originators Only campaign launched a series of exclusive collaborative colorways. The HesKicks x Grid 9000 'Originators Only’ features a grey-based suede upper with black suede overlays on the mudguard. The sneaker also sports lavender details on the plush lower eyelet, black leather on the wrap-around tongue, and reflective silver accents on the side S-shaped design and heel counter.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Originators DJ Delz Miami Nights
Saucony Grid SD Originators Bull1trc Big Trouble In Little China
Saucony Grid SD Originators EddieWinKicks 97 Taurus
data.story: In 2016, Saucony Originals enlisted a diverse group of 10 creators from the digital sneaker community to create their own designs for the Originators Only project. Sneaker blogger eddiewinkicks based his version of the Grid SD on his first car, a green 1997 Ford Taurus, resulting in this colorway that blends tan perforated suede with deep green leather. The shoe also boasts a green suede tongue, tan leather lining, an embroidered 'e.win' on the ankle, a speckled midsole, and tan outsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Originators Foamer Simpson Bubba Gump
data.story: Teaming up with sneaker lover Mr. Foamer Simpson, Saucony released an exclusive edition of the Grid silhouette as part of its Originators Only collection. The MrFoamerSimpson x Grid SD 'Originators Only' features a red suede upper with darker red suede overlays throughout. The sneaker also boasts a white lacing system for contrast, a padded collar for comfort, and a cushioned midsole for a supportive fit.

data.name: Saucony Grid 8000 Bodega Classifieds
data.story: Boston-based brand Bodega has teamed up with Saucony to release an exclusive colorway that draws from the classic aesthetic of 1990s footwear. The Bodega x Grid 8000 'Classifieds' features a yellow suede-based upper with black suede overlays, red mesh panels, and white nylon. The sneaker also sports patent red leather accents along the branded heel, as well as a full-length rubber midsole with G.R.I.D cushioning for added comfort. Keep an eye out for Bodega’s own classifieds printed on the tongue patch.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Summer Nights
data.story: The Summer Nights rendition of the Grid SD runner pays homage to the colorful summer sunsets, featuring vibrant shades of orange and navy on the suede upper. Colorful pops of yellow, purple, and pink appear between the Saucony branding. Underfoot comfort and durability come by way of Grid technology in the midsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Originators YoAnty Fenway
Saucony Grid SD Originators Sneakershouts Portuguese Gold
data.story: Saucony teamed up with a series of Instagram-famous influencers in 2017 for the Originators Only collection, five different releases of the Grid SD limited to 100 pairs each. Sneakershouts’ ‘Portuguese Gold’ rendition of the retro runner features a combination of black and grey suedes on the upper, while metallic gold accents emerge on the branding, heel and midsole speckling.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Originators SITB Golden Gates
data.story: Saucony’s Originators Only collection calls on YouTube influencers to design unique colorways. The SneakerHeadInTheBay x Grid SD 'Originators Only' features a Charcoal Grey suede upper with padding along the collar. As a nod to the Bay Area, the sneaker also sports gold and burgundy overlays in patent and matte leather. Other design details include waxed laces, a branded tongue patch, and branding along the heel and sidewall.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Originators TonyD2Wild Tiger
data.story: Lexington, Massachusetts-based brand Saucony teamed up with five Instagram-famous sneakerheads to release the first sneaker of the Originators Only project. ToNYD2WiLD x Grid SD 'Originators Only' features an upper dressed in orange, with speckled black detailing throughout. The sneaker also boasts a tiger logo on the tongue and a jagged-tooth outsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Originators TBlake Triple White
data.story: The TylerJBlake x Grid SD ‘Originators Only’ released in August 2017 as part of a larger Saucony collaboration drawing on the talents of a select group of influencers. Tyler J Blake’s contribution takes the form of a Triple White Grid SD. Built with an all-leather upper and limited to just 100 pairs, the retro runner is meant to function as something of a blank canvas designed to be customized.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 The Good Will Out VHS
data.story: The Good Will Out taps into 90s nostalgia with a VHS-inspired offering of Saucony’s Shadow 5000. The shoe features black suede and mesh paneling throughout the upper, with leather trim accents on the heel and branding. VHS color bars are rendered on the heel and tongue, while rewind, fast-forward, stop and play buttons are embroidered on the toe. The packaging is equipped with a custom layout that implements a design reminiscent of a VCR.

data.name: Saucony Freedom Runner Suede Olive
data.story: Saucony’s Freedom Runner emerges with a retro running aesthetic constructed with an olive green suede throughout the upper. Etched with perforations on the toe and quarter panel for breathability, the shoe also implements Saucony’s grid pattern on the white midsole. A translucent blue tone finishes the rippled outsole.

data.name: Freedom Runner 'Suede'
data.story: Saucony’s Freedom Runner appears with a minimalist makeup that utilizes a premium black suede application throughout the upper, while micro-perforations along the toe and tongue promote breathability. Constructed with an EVERUN midsole that’s accented with the brand’s familiar grid design, the sneaker also implements a translucent blue tone on the rippled outsole, with D-ring eyelets on the eyestay.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Bricks
data.story: This Saucony Shadow 5000 ‘Bricks’ draws inspiration from the brick buildings of Harvard and the brick pathway of Boston’s Freedom Trail, featuring laser-etched brick detailing on the toe, tongue and heel. It also features a deep maroon suede on the upper, while a leather badge on the tongue is modeled after the golden plaques marking historical sites on the Freedom Trail.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Sneakers76 the Legend of God Taras
data.story: Italian sneaker brand Sneakers76 released a colorway inspired by the picturesque scenes of their hometown, Taranto. Designed in collaboration with Saucony, the Sneakers76 x Shadow 5000 'The Legend of God Taras' gets its name from Greek mythology, which tells the story of Poseidon as the founder of Taranto. The low-top features a premium suede upper with grey, blue, red and white panels dispersed throughout. The sneaker also sports a wood-coated tab on the midsole and trident-debossed tongues.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Sparring
data.story: Limited to just 1,200 pairs, this Saucony Grid 9000 ‘Sparring’ released as a European-exclusive in January 2017. It features a bootie construction with blue suede panels based on a boxing ring’s canvas mat and a boxing glove-inspired red on the forefoot suede and mesh. It also comes with metallic gold accents on the Saucony side stripes and the heel. Underfoot, an EVA midsole with speckled gold detailing gives way to a gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Low Vegan Charcoal Orange
Saucony G9 Control Neon Nights Black
data.story: Saucony revives heritage design details from their archives of performance runners to create the G9 Control silhouette for the Neon Nights iteration, which features a combination of premium suedes and leathers on the upper. The black and charcoal color scheme is contrasted with neon pink accents on the branding, eyelets, and heel, while the GRID 9000 cushioning system delivers long-lasting comfort.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD No Chill Light Green
Saucony Shadow 6000 HT White Black
data.story: Initially released in 1992, the Shadow 6000 silhouette has undergone a series of updates that enhance comfort and boost performance. The Shadow 6000 HT features a premium white perforated leather upper for ultimate breathability and solid white leather overlays. Other design details include a black suede mudguard, beige details on the inner lining, an EVA midsole for lightweight cushioning, and a triangular lug gum rubber outsole for superior traction.

data.name: Saucony Courageous Feature Bacon and Eggs
data.story: Saucony’s preference for collaborating with independent sneaker boutiques continued in 2016, when it joined forces with Feature to create this breakfast-themed edition of the Courageous silhouette. The Las Vegas retailer opted for a ‘Bacon & Eggs’ motif, with the retro runner featuring satin and washed suede uppers in egg-white and pink hues. The Saucony ‘S’ logo, in pink leather on the lateral side, is punctuated with a trio of yellow dots, an allusion to egg yolks. Feature branding appears on the heel, while the insoles are printed with bacon and eggs graphics.

data.name: Extra Butter x Shadow 5000 'For the People - Friends and Family'
data.story: This is the friends-and-family edition of the Extra Butter x Shadow 5000 ‘For the People,’ a social-media project in which the New York-based retailer allowed fans to ultimately select the design of the Saucony shoe. Limited to just 200 pairs, this model features a leather build in white, tan and red hues, accented with Extra Butter branding on the tongue tag and heel panel.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 Extra Butter For the People
data.story: Saucony and New York sneaker boutique Extra Butter tapped into the social media response of the shoe store’s followers. Identified as the ‘For the People,’ this Shadow 5000 offering is equipped with a drive-in movie theme that’s formed with pastel hues throughout the wolverine pigskin suede panels, patent leather accent on the heel and a full-grain leather sockliner. The tongue logo features a pink dice design, while the name ‘Extra Butter’ is embroidered onto the heels in a retro Cadillac font.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD Pumpkin Spice
data.story: Released just in time to celebrate the season of pumpkin spice lattes, the Grid SD 'Pumpkin Spice' celebrates Halloween the only way Saucony knows how: with a brand new colorway. The sneaker features a Pumpkin Spice-colored leather and suede upper with metallic orange accents throughout the shoe. The sneaker also sports a two-tone midsole and a barista symbol on the tongue as a nod to roasted coffee beans, a silk suede perforated toe box, and Saucony’s signature G.R.I.D. cushioning system.

data.name: Shadow 5000 'Sushi Pack'
data.story: Inspired by the traditional Japanese meal, the Shadow 5000 ‘Sushi Pack’ released in July 2015 as part of a three-piece set from Saucony. This special-edition colorway of the retro runner features a mesh and suede upper finished in a blend of bright green and black, referencing wasabi and soy sauce. Contrasting accents take the form of Saucony’s vector logo rendered in white, along with pops of red on the lining and heel.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Black
data.story: Originally released in 1994, the Saucony Grid 9000 boasts an inner bootie construction, an EVA midsole and a translucent outsole with visible GRID system cushioning. The Saucony Grid 9000 ‘Micro Dot’ dropped in a 2016 two-pack alongside a white colorway. Combining nylon, suede and neoprene on the upper, the shoe’s black base is accented by white microdot detailing and mint green accents.

data.name: Saucony Grid 8000 Shrimp Scampi
data.story: Inspired by shrimp scampi, the Saucony Grid 8000 ‘Shrimp Scampi’ represents the dish with its light pink, green and beige color palette. Constructed with a combination of suede and pebbled leather throughout the upper, the shoe is splashed with green accents on the eyelets and branding, while a pink splatter lines the GRID midsole.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 5000 The Quiet Life the Quiet Shadow
data.story: Los Angeles streetwear label The Quiet Life teamed up with Saucony in 2016 for a galaxy-themed version of the heritage sneaker brand’s Shadow 5000 silhouette. The Quiet Life x Saucony Shadow 5000 ‘Cosmos’ features nylon and nubuck construction. The eponymous print is showcased on the midfoot panel, while embossed ‘Quiet Life’ lettering sits below another starry strip on the heel. The Quiet Life and Saucony co-branding appears on the tongue.

data.name: "Saucony Grid 9000 Premier ""Street Sweets"""
data.story: The 'Street Sweets Delicious' edition of the Saucony Grid 9000 is the handiwork of Michigan skate-and-apparel store Premier. Dressed in a taffy-style colorway, the sneaker features elastic laces complete with adjustable toggle, leather and suede overlays and a candy cane print on the insole. The neoprene tongue, branded with a candy-striped ‘P,’ forms part of the interior bootie construction. The pastel upper is supported by a thick EVA midsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid Sd Premium Shoes Berry/Black
data.story: Originally released in 1991, the Saucony Grid SD was the first to introduce the athletic brand's landmark cushioning system. This upgraded variant retools original materials with a suede, synthetic leather and mesh upper in a modern color block look. Supportive TPU straps and a reflective heel provide classic functionality. The sculpted, shock-absorbent midsole is installed above a bicolor Shadow 5000 outsole with triangular lugs.

data.name: Grid SD 'Derby Pack'
data.story: Saucony’s Grid SD originally released in 1981, incorporating the brand’s Ground Reaction Inertia Device (GRID) technology in the midsole to improve cushioning. The shoe features a combination of suede, leather and mesh panels in purple and light blue tones throughout, while the outsole implements a rugged traction pattern for grip on a variety of surfaces.

data.name: Saucony Shadow 6000 Burgundy Suede (Packer Shoes)
data.story: This tonal burgundy colorway of the Saucony Shadow 6000 launched in April 2016 as a Packer Shoes exclusive. The retro runner carries an all-suede upper, featuring perforated detailing on the toe box, quarter panel and tongue, which ditches the customary logo patch. A textured, crisp white midsole gives way to a gum rubber outsole, reinforced with triangular lugs for added traction and durability.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Letterman
data.story: With the Grid 9000 ‘Letterman,’ Saucony restyles its classic runner with a build inspired by traditional varsity jackets. The upper combines fuzzy grey heathered wool and black nappa leather, mounted atop a lightly speckled white midsole and gum rubber outsole. A chenille ‘S’ on the tongue is reminiscent of school patches, while the ‘1898’ heel embroidery gives the nod to the year Saucony was founded.

data.name: "Saucony Shadow 5500 Bait ""Cruel World 6"""
data.story: Designed to encourage children to pursue their dreams and look to the stars for inspiration, this BAIT and Saucony collaboration is part of a more significant effort to aid children suffering from disabilities. The BAIT x Shadow 5500 'Cruel World 6: Giant Leaps' features a black mesh-based upper with black leather overlays on the mudguard, heel, and eyestay. Speckled 3M white leather overlays serve as a nod to the moon’s surface and a NASA-inspired graphic completes the look.

data.name: "Saucony Grid 9000 Shoe Gallery ""Locals Only"""
data.story: At the beginning of 2016, Miami-based apparel and footwear retailer Shoe Gallery dropped this technicolor rendition of the Saucony Grid 9000. Taking inspiration from the neon boards, bright branding and sun-baked aesthetics of 80s surf culture, the ‘Locals Only’ collab boasts numerous shades across its multi-panel construction. The predominant hue is a sandy Off-White, a reminder that the beach itself is the main driver behind the design.

data.name: Bodega x Shadow 5000
data.story: This Bodega x Shadow 5000 is drawn from a ‘Reissue’ Pack from January 2016, featuring two of the four original colorways of a Japanese-exclusive collaboration released in 2010. Saucony’s retro runner is given an all-blue color scheme, executed on a leather and suede upper with breathable mesh on the toe box. An Off-White midsole gives way to a gum rubber outsole underfoot.

data.name: Shadow 6000 Suede 'Irish Coffee'
data.story: In the winter of 1943, a flight departed from Foynes Air Base in County Limerick, Ireland, for Newfoundland, Canada, but was forced to turn back due to bad weather. To comfort the passengers, the head chef at the restaurant in the terminal building, Joe Sheridan, added a splash of Irish whiskey to their coffees, serving up the world’s first Irish coffee. In 2015, Saucony paid tribute to Sheridan’s invention with a three-shoe Irish Coffee Pack representing the three main ingredients: coffee, whiskey and cream. This Shadow 6000 Suede 'Irish Coffee’ is the cream iteration. It features a tonal cream Wolverine Silkee suede upper with perforated detailing, a crisp white EVA midsole and a rugged triangular lug rubber outsole.

data.name: "Saucony Grid 9000 END ""White Noise"""
data.story: Inspired by the days of analog TV, the END x Grid 9000 ‘White Noise’ released in November 2015 as a collaboration between Saucony and the UK retailer. The retro runner features mixed materials across the upper, including fuzzy wool on the toe box and textile overlays in a ‘noisy’ pattern that mimics an analog TV screen when the signal cuts out. Bleached Aqua accents deliver contrasting pops of color throughout the upper and outsole.

data.name: Just Blaze x Packer x Grid SD 'Casino'
data.story: Through his October 2015 sneaker collaboration with Packer Shoes and Saucony, renowned hip-hop producer Just Blaze celebrated one of his greatest passions—vintage Ralph Lauren apparel. Specifically, the shoe’s design is inspired by a woven Polo shirt emblazoned with a roulette-wheel graphic. The red, green and yellow color palette of the garment is repeated on the shoe, which is built with a combination of suede and rip-stop nylon.

data.name: "Saucony Grid SD Packer Shoes Just Blaze ""Casino"""
Grid 9000
data.story: Saucony brings back their signature Grid 9000 model from the 90s, featuring a mono-sockliner design that wraps the midfoot. The rest of the upper is formed with a combination of mesh, suede and leather panels that display white, orange and navy tones. The brand’s G.R.I.D. technology in the midsole and a triangular shaped traction pattern are included for cushioning and grip, respectively.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD No Chill Pack Yellow
data.story: Adding to their collection of retro releases, Saucony dropped the Grid SD 'No Chill' pack in August 2015. The collection is a summer-inspired, four-shoe collection that stays true to its retro style with sleek updates. Dressed in a vibrant hue, the suede shoe is outfitted with perforations for lightweight ventilation. The Grid midsole delivers premium cushioning and stability below.

data.name: Saucony Grid SD No Chill Pack Light Blue
"Saucony Grid SD Sneaker Freaker ""Kushwacker"""
data.story: A follow up to the Aussie magazine’s 2012 Saucony Grid 9000 ‘Bushwhacker,’ the Sneaker Freaker Grid SD ‘Kushwacker’ takes its inspiration from a strand of the good herb known as Purple Haze. The upper features a blend of black mesh and purple suede with beige form stripes complimenting the sole unit. It also comes with a Saucony branded grey suede heel panel, black TPU eyestays, and 3M reflective detailing.

data.name: "Saucony Shadow 5000 Epitome ""Big Fish"""
data.story: The Atlanta Fish Market has been made famous by the 65-foot fish statue residing in its parking lot. Atlanta-based independent fashion boutique Epitome, which set up shop across the street, decided to honor the restaurant with ‘The Righteous One.’ A 2015 collaboration with Saucony, the shoe features a suede and leather version of the Shadow 5000 complete with a fish-scale pattern across the toe box and an illustration of the ‘Big Fish’ on the insole. Two Middle Eastern motifs, a hamsa and eye of conscience, share space with the design’s nods to the unique landmark.

data.name: Saucony DXN Trainer Blue Green
data.story: Part of Saucony’s Bermuda Pack, the DXN Trainer surfaces with blue and teal tones throughout the upper’s suede construction to symbolize the clear waters of the tropical island. The silhouette was renowned marathoner Rod Dixon’s shoe of choice during the early 80s, featuring a low to the ground midsole unit that’s paired with perforated paneling on the side and toe.

data.name: Saucony G9 Shadow 6 Scoops Pack Vanilla Strawberry
data.story: Saucony tapped into their rich heritage of running silhouettes for the G9 Shadow ‘Strawberry Vanilla Ice Cream.’ The dessert-themed release is completed with tan details and speckled (or sprinkled) white soles. A premium suede upper features different shades of ‘Strawberry Vanilla’ and a graphic of two spoons adorns the tongue tab as well as the shoebox.

data.name: "Saucony Grid 9000 End ""Red Noise"""
data.story: END. teamed up with US-based brand Saucony to release an exclusive update to the classic RED/NOISE silhouette, which draws from Robert Brown’s theory of the random and rapid movement of particles. The End x Grid 9000 'Red Noise' features a woven cotton, felt, and wool upper with ballistic nylon overlays in a gradient red color scheme. The sneaker also boasts 3M reflective rope laces, jersey lining, and G.R.I.D technology in the midsole for responsive cushioning.

data.name: Saucony G9 Shadow 6 Bodega Pattern Recognition Grey
data.story: The Saucony Elite collaboration with Bodega pays tribute to the wild patterns of the 90s with the ‘Pattern Recognition,’ which released as part of a larger capsule. Featuring a grey suede and mesh construction up top, a tonal leopard-spotted pattern emerges on the underlays, with a geometric print on the midsole. Assembled with grey suede and mesh panels on the upper, the shoe is juxtaposed with a combination of Mint and black hues on the overlays, collar and midsole. data.name: "Saucony Shadow Master UBIQ ""Atlantic Tide"""

data.name: "Saucony G9 Shadow 5 Feature ""Pumpkin"""
data.story: In 2015 Las Vegas sneaker boutique Feature paired with Saucony to create the High Roller pack of three Sin City inspired sneakers. The final sneaker in the Feature x Saucony collaboration, The Pumpkin pulls it’s design and name from the $1,000 gambling chip. The upper is constructed of smooth suede panels imitating the chip’s orange and green tones with 3M reflective accents on the heel and tongue. Feature’s logo and “All Things Good” motto is written across a chip embroidered on the shoe’s tongue. At the time of its release, The Pumpkin was available exclusively at Feature’s shop and website.

data.name: "Saucony Shadow 6000 Bait ""Cruel World 5"""
data.story: Originally released as part of an effort to aid Water.org, which aims to provide clean water to communities across the globe, the Saucony Shadow 6000 x Bait 'Cruel World 5' reflects its charity of choice with an aquatic blue-oriented colorway. The sneaker features leather linings and insole for premium comfort, with a tonal blue mesh and suede upper. A speckled foam midsole adds to the look while providing soft, lightweight cushioning.

data.name: "Saucony G9 Shadow 6 Feature ""The Barney"""
data.story: The second release in the 2015 G9 Shadow 6 High Roller collaboration between Feature LV and Saucony, ‘The Barney’ sports a distinctive purple colorway inspired by the strip’s $500 casino chip known by the same name. Layered in tonal purple, the design features a premium suede upper accompanied by black suede overlays, a 3M heel panel, side guards, and speckled round laces over a speckled midsole and gum outsole. Saucony’s dot logo and Feature’s motto, “All Things Good,” come together on casino chip graphics found on the tongue label and insoles.

data.name: Saucony Grid 9000 Mint
data.story: Saucony’s Grid 9000 runner, which first appeared in 1994, gets refreshed with a mint and teal makeup throughout the upper. The suede and mesh textiles that make up the design are accented by hits of black. The shoe also features a mono-sockliner that wraps the foot, while the thick white midsole provides contrast.

data.name: "Saucony G9 Shadow 6 Feature ""High Roller"""
data.story: Las Vegas-based sneaker boutique Feature teamed up with Saucony to release the G9 Shadow 6 ‘High Roller’ in December 2014. Inspired by a $100 casino chip, the lifestyle runner features a combination of black suede and perforated white leather on the upper, accented with pops of pink and reflective 3M detailing. A casino chip emblem graces the tongue, accompanied by Feature’s ‘All Things Good’ tagline.

data.name: "Saucony Grid 9000 Play Cloths ""Motocross"""

Other signature details include a Motocross tongue logo and embroidered “077” on the toe as a nod to Pusha T’s birth year.

data.name: "Saucony Shadow Master UBIQ ""Pacific Dusk"""

The Ubiq x Shadow Master 'Pacific Dusk' features a two-tone perforated suede upper dressed in red and orange. The sneaker also boasts contrasting black Saucony-branded details along the sides, tongue and on the outsole, as well as pink details on the plastic heel cap and lace locks.

data.name: Saucony G9 Control Wine
data.story: The Saucony G9 Control sneaker is a hybridized expression of heritage design inspired by the Grid 9000. Introduced in 2015, this 'Wine' version's upper employs monochromatic layers of suede and leather and tonal lacing. Dotted cutouts, heel branding and the retro tongue label pick up a contrast hue. Tricolored midsole cushioning and a full-length rubber outsole reissue classic athletic performance.

Saucony Grid 8500 MD Boro
data.story: The Saucony Grid 8500 Boro is a contemporary interpretation of the Japanese practice of preserving and repurposing traditional textiles. Argyle-patterned textile and twill shape the upper, with an extended neoprene tongue cushioning the interior. Contrast suede panels layer the heel and midfoot. The signature midsole hosts a responsive GRID cushioning system. Triangular lugs are equipped on the rubber outsole.

Saucony Hurricane Iso Silver
data.story: Designed for maximum cushioning and stability, the Saucony Hurricane ISO 'Silver Carbon' sneaker is made for neutral runners. The breathable mesh upper is reinforced by a heel frame and its ISOFIT lacing system that conforms to the foot. The PWRGRID+ midsole and 8mm offset outsole deliver premium underfoot comfort and support.

data.name: Jazz Hook And Loop Toddler 'Navy Red'
Wmns Liberty Iso 'Red Black'
data.story: Giving women's runners the freedom they deserve, the Saucony Wmns Liberty Iso 'Red Black' enhances every stride with its tech-savvy design. The acclaimed sneaker was awarded one of 'The 12 Best New Running Shoes of Winter 2018' by Gear Patrol due to its combination of an ISOFIT system, engineered mesh upper with FLEXFILM and medial TPU piece. Adding to the innovative appeal, an EVERUN topsole and midsole are set up to propel the foot forward from below.

data.name: Saucony Kinvara 7 Pink/Purple-Blue (W)
data.story: Designed for female runners, the Saucony Wmns Kinvara 7 is unveiled in a 'Pink' shade for this rendition. The sleek sneaker hones in on flexible comfort with an engineered mesh upper with FLEXFILM technology to create a fit that conforms to the movement of the foot. Bolstering cushion, an EVERUN heel insert magnifies energy return and works with an extra-supportive foam midsole below. The silhouette rests atop a TRI-FLEX outsole for grip on varying terrain.

Wmns Zealot Iso 2 Reflex
data.story: The Saucony Wmns Zealot Iso 2 Reflex sneaker updates the first iteration of the performance runner. Lightweight and durable, the mesh upper features synthetic, lace through overlays and an ISOFIT system to summon structure and a snug fit in this women's version. An EVERUN topsole bridges the gap between the upper and the cushioned midsole underfoot, taking on a black and white, layered look. At the heel, 'Saucony' lettering calls out the brand while a signature three-dot design appears on the toe.

data.name: Wmns Jazz Original 'Off-White Denim'
data.story: Fashion-forward and stylish, the Saucony Wmns Jazz Original 'Off-White Denim,' transforms the iconic 1980s original into a street-ready design. Adding an extra dimension of oomph to the recognizable silhouette, the upper is presented with blue denim at the heel and toe and an Off-White midsole and three-dot logo at the midfoot. A speckled EVA foam midsole attenuates impact and joins forces with a gum rubber outsole for a traction-ready swagger.

data.name: Peregrine 5
data.story: Built to withstand rugged trails, the Saucony Peregrine 5 sneaker wears a dynamic Orange, Citron and Blue color palette. The low-profile sneaker is designed with a flexible and durable FLEXFILM upper to support multi-directional movement. Heading down below, a rock plate at the midfoot and forefoot maintain stability while POWERGRID technology delivers massive cushion in the heel. XT-900 rubber offers high-traction underfoot to finalize the design.

data.name: Shadow 6000 'Black Coffee'
data.story: A cornerstone of the brand's running heritage, the Saucony Shadow 6000 made its name as a favorite among Olympic runners in the 90s. The Saucony Shadow 6000 'Black Coffee' continues the heritage as an OG lifestyle shoe. The perforated suede upper comes dipped totally in black, topped by tonal overlays, including the classic Saucony three-dot logo on the side. The white midsole boasts an Ionic Cushioning System for soft support above a gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Little Kids Kotaro
data.story: Ready for wear at the playground or at school, the Saucony Little Kids Kotaro is designed for growing strides. The vibrant, multi-colored upper is built with a mesh base and a web-like leather overlay to keep the foot in place. Pink laces match the three-dot branding at the midfoot and the outsole down below. To keep the grip, rubber pods are places in the highest-impact areas, thus reducing weight and increasing stability for play.

data.name: Hurricane ISO 2 'Grey Charcoal Orange'
data.story: Building upon the innovative running design of its predecessor, the Saucony Hurricane ISO 2 'Grey Charcoal Orange' sneaker updates the original with increased comfort and support. The shoe is outfitted with an ISOFIT mesh upper, providing adaptable fit and stability. The EVERUN midsole and heel landing zone absorb impact, while the TRI-FLEX and XT-900 carbon outsole offer durable wear.

data.name: Wmns Jazz Original
data.story: Ready for fall, the Wmns Jazz Original shows off an orange and purple color palette for this contemporary iteration of a 1980s staple. The lifestyle sneaker is geared toward women and calls upon nylon and suede to construct the two-toned upper. Increasing comfort on the inside, a padded tongue and collar work with a traditional lacing system to secure the fit. The low-profile sneaker is armed with a substantial EVA foam midsole for maximum energy return below.

data.name: DXN Trainer CL 'White Black'
data.story: Reinterpreting the long-distance DXN Trainer, the Saucony DXN Trainer CL 'White Black' sneaker remains true to the original's 1983 silhouette with contemporary updates. This premium version is outfitted with a smooth leather upper and plush suede overlays. The low-cut, padded collar and tongue provide enhanced comfort. The protective rubber sole offers durability underfoot.

Jazz Low Pro
data.story: Known its for uncomplicated style, the 1981 Saucony Jazz is a classic running sneaker that transcends time. The Jazz Low Pro is designed similarly to its predecessor, but with a slimmed down sole. The shoe is constructed of a durable nylon upper, reinforced by suede overlays. Shock-absorbing, low-profile EVA foam and a XT-600 lug rubber outsole work together for cushioned durability.

data.name: Saucony Grid Stability MC Wide White/Silver-Gold
Wmns Shadow 6000
data.story: Tapping into the ethos of the early 1990s, the updated Saucony Wmns Shadow 6000 brings a retro vibe to the classic lifestyle sneaker. The predominantly white base in this women's model, sees cutouts for mesh paneling at the toe and nylon on the sides, while leather overlays provide structure all-around. Offering a bit of color and reinforcement, grey and purple panels cover the base of the upper. A bulky EVA midsole comforts the foot underneath, creating a platform for longer mileage.

data.name: Shadow Original
data.story: The modern era of Saucony dates back to 1983, when Ron Dixon won the New York City Marathon while wearing a pair of Saucony Shadows. A contemporary retro iteration, the Saucony Shadow Original has a blue upper in mesh with suede overlays. Yellow hits on the collar, heel, tongue and midsole add contrast, along with brand's famous three-dot logo on the side. Below, a low-profile midsole and black rubber outsole add OG style.

data.name: Saucony Jazz 4000 Boston Children's Hospital Kieran
DXN Trainer
data.story: The old school Saucony DXN Trainer has been updated for a modern generation, uniting the best elements of the era with contemporary design. The reimagined long-distance running shoe is constructed with a durable, nylon upper reinforced with plush suede overlays. The low-cut padded collar and cushioned tongue offer natural movement. Below, the durable sole offers traction.

data.name: Saucony Jazz Original Dark Grey Rose Violet (W)
Saucony Grid 8000 Footpatrol X Beams Only In Tokyo
Grid 9000 'Burgundy'
data.story: One of the most innovative and groundbreaking running designs in the early 90s, the Grid 9000 paved the way for future Saucony trainers. This rendition pays tribute to its original roots while remixing it with contemporary comfort. The Grid 9000 'Burgundy' sneaker features a breathable mesh upper reinforced by synthetic overlays. Underfoot, lightweight cushioning and a durable outsole provide comfort and traction.

data.name: Shadow 5000 'White Chocolate'
data.story: Saucony, which was founded in 1898, can trace its roots to Cambridge, Massachusetts, a city whose history of candy-making dates back to 1765. The sportswear brand pays tribute to this heritage with the ‘White Chocolate’ iteration of the Shadow 5000. The runner features leather and suede uppers above a speckled EVA midsole. Metallic gold accents dot the silhouette, with embroidered Saucony lettering on the heel.

data.name: Wmns Shadow 5000
data.story: The Saucony Wmns Shadow 5000 celebrates the legacy of the Boston-based brand. The 80s was a break-out decade for Saucony, releasing the OG Shadow 5000 just four years after the Original silhouette. Debuting in a modern Grey and Light Green color scheme, the women's runner preserves the nylon and suede upper seen in the original versions. A mesh toe and heel contribute to breathability and lightweight function while a substantial EVA midsole and grippy outsole support foot from below.

data.name: Wmns Shadow Original
data.story: The Saucony Shadow Original made its debut in 1985. Taking on the nostalgic look, this modern Wmns Blue and Bright Green rendition mimics similar design features as its counterpart from decades ago. The women's sneaker is built with nylon, mesh and suede to compose the layered upper and reveals a neon green liner and recognizable three-dot logo on the sidewall for a boost of color. Delivering on-demand traction below, a Maxitrac triangular lug outsole focuses on grip strength.

data.name: Shadow Master
data.story: Tracing its beginnings to Saucony Creek, Pennsylvania, Saucony's history includes making boots for the US Army during World War II and the first Space Walk before designing the shoes worn by Rod Dixon when he won the 1983 New York City Marathon. That running heritage carries through the retro Saucony Shadow Master. The blue and grey upper comes in mesh with suede and leather overlays, plus the brand's well known three-dot logo on the midpanel.

Wmns Bullet Vegan
data.story: Designed with females in mind, the Saucony Women Bullet Vegan is an eco-friendly sneaker from the Massachusetts-based brand. The shoe features an all-canvas upper and joins the Jazz Low Pro Vegan in an effort to source materials responsibly. Decked out in black, a pink, three-dot 'S' logo accents the midfoot while a textile liner in neon green comforts the foot and adds a boost of color inside. Taking on the look of the Original track shoe, the slimmed-down sole unit cradles the foot below.

data.name: Shadow Original
data.story: Saucony first began as a children's shoe company in the late 1800s, transitioning over time to a running and streetwear brand. The Saucony Shadow Original is a retro runner made for the streets. The tri-tone upper alternates between red, black and a yellow-beige, with a mesh base and multiple suede and leather overlays. Below, the compact midsole and outsole add to a vintage vibe.

data.name: Shadow Original 'Balsam'
data.story: After making a name for itself in the 80s and 90s as a supplier of premium running shoes, Saucony's retro silhouettes have become streetwear staples. The Saucony Shadow Original 'Balsam' is a heritage style that features an eye-catching tri-tonal colorway, highlighted by suede green overlays and the brand's famous three-dot logo.

data.name: Shadow 6000 'Arc'
data.story: Released in 2008 as part of a limited-edition, three-sneaker collab with ALIFE Rivington Club, the Shadow 6000 'Arc' features a 90s silhouette in classic 80s colors. The upper comes in white mesh with a deep blue on the mudguard and Saucony three-dot logo. The exaggerated tongue features a striped patch with A.R.C. branding, and it all sits atop a thick foam midsole and black rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Grid 8500 MD Blue Denim
data.story: The Saucony Grid 8500 blends the allure of hybridized design with street-ready style. This 'Boro' interpretation tells the historical narrative of Japanese textiles through a pre-aged denim upper with a contoured twill mudguard, tonal suede heel and neoprene bootie. Minimalist branding sits on the pull tab. The GRID midsole cushioning system and durable rubber outsole speak to the sneaker's athletic legacy.

data.name: Saucony Jazz 4000 Boston Children's Hospital Luc
Bullet
data.story: Originally created as a lightweight track shoe in 1985, the Saucony Bullet was repurposed as a lifestyle design. The shoe is fitted with a durable nylon upper, supported by structured suede overlays. The soft fabric lining, along with the padded collar and EVA midsole, provide the foot with cushioned comfort. A rubber outsole completes the streamlined style.

data.name: Shadow 6000 'Gray Pack'
data.story: The Saucony Shadow 6000 has stood the test of time since its debut as a 90s running shoe. As part of a four-sneaker pack released in 2014, the Saucony Shadow 6000 'Gray Pack' shows the sneaker's evolution into a lifestyle go-to. The upper comes with a mesh base, topped by premium pigskin suede overlays in a rich green. The classic Saucony three-dot logo lands on the side, with further branding on the tongue and heel. Below, an Ionic Cushioning System adds support atop a gum rubber outsole.

data.name: Saucony Zealot Iso 2 Blue/Orange
data.story: Designed to take you from road to gym, the Saucony Zealot Iso 2 is a versatile runner equipped with innovation. Unveiled in a blue and orange colorway, the upper integrates a mesh and synthetic system with FLEXFILM technology to improve structure up top. The tongue is incorporated into the upper, giving the shoe a slip-on feel while an ISOFIT design keeps the foot in place. Down below, the sole unit is presented with an EVERUN topsole and Powergrid+ cushioning system accompanied by a rubber outsole.
